    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Once very hot, add your <strong>steak[s]</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> cornflour</strong> in a measuring jug with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[270ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>black bean paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>ginger paste</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and mix until smooth \u2013 this is your<strong> black bean sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>steak[s]</strong> is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest and reserve the pan</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>sweet pea pods</strong>, <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper strips</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once beginning to soften, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>black bean sauce </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until thickened \u2013 these are your <strong>black bean vegetables</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak[s]</strong> finely on a clean board</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-steak-with-black-bean-veg-and-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced steak </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice </strong>with the <strong>black bean vegetables </strong>to the side</p><p>Spoon any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>black bean sauce </strong>over the steak and garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
